  "output": "## Test coverage analysis — jobsquare\n\n**Baseline: 0%.** There is no `tests/` directory, no test files anywhere in the repo, and `pytest` isn't even in `requirements.txt`. Every one of the ~2,500 lines across `models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `pipeline.py`, `notify.py`, `cli.py`, `agent.py`, and `fetchers.py` (19 ATS integrations) is unexercised by automated tests.\n\nBelow: gaps by module, the specific edge cases the code already anticipates (via comments) but doesn't verify, and skeletons to close them. I'd suggest `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio` + `httpx.MockTransport` (no network needed) as the harness — add to `requirements.txt` / a new `requirements-dev.txt`.\n\n---\n\n### `tests/conftest.py` (shared fixtures — write this first)\n\n```python\nimport pytest\nimport httpx\nfrom store import Store\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\ndef store(tmp_path):\n    \"\"\"Fresh on-disk sqlite store per test — Store doesn't support :memory: across cursors reliably here.\"\"\"\n    with Store(tmp_path / \"test.db\") as s:\n        yield s\n\n\ndef make_transport(handler):\n    \"\"\"handler(request) -> httpx.Response, for MockTransport-backed fetchers.\"\"\"\n    return httpx.MockTransport(handler)\n```\n\n---\n\n### `models.py` — `parse_posted_at`, `Job`\n\nPure functions, zero excuse not to have 100% coverage. Currently untested entirely, including the two format branches the docstring explicitly calls out (Lever ms-epoch vs. others).\n\n```python\n# tests/test_models.py\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timezone\nfrom models import Job, parse_posted_at\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"value,expected\", [\n    (\"\", None),\n    (None, None),\n    (\"1643241332430\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),  # Lever ms\n    (\"1643241332\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),      # seconds\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32Z\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32+00:00\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),\n    (\"2022-01-26T22:55:32\", datetime(2022, 1, 26, 22, 55, 32, tzinfo=timezone.utc)),  # naive -> assumed UTC\n    (\"Posted 3 Days Ago\", None),   # Workday prose — unparseable, must not raise\n    (\"not a date\", None),\n    (\"-100\", datetime(1970, 1, 1, tzinfo=timezone.utc) - __import__(\"datetime\").timedelta(seconds=100)),  # negative epoch\n])\ndef test_parse_posted_at(value, expected):\n    assert parse_posted_at(value) == expected\n\n\ndef test_job_key_is_stable_across_edits():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"123\", title=\"A\", url=\"u\")\n    key = j.key\n    j.title = \"Changed Title\"\n    assert j.key == key == \"lever:acme:123\"\n\n\ndef test_job_content_hash_changes_on_material_fields():\n    base = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u1\", location=\"NYC\", department=\"Eng\")\n    same = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u1\", location=\"NYC\", department=\"Eng\")\n    moved = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u1\", location=\"SF\", department=\"Eng\")\n    assert base.content_hash == same.content_hash\n    assert base.content_hash != moved.content_hash\n\n\ndef test_job_to_row_excludes_raw_and_adds_derived_fields():\n    j = Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\", raw={\"secret\": 1})\n    row = j.to_row()\n    assert \"raw\" not in row\n    assert row[\"key\"] == j.key\n    assert row[\"content_hash\"] == j.content_hash\n```\n\n**Untested edge case worth flagging:** `parse_posted_at`'s epoch branch does `n = int(s)` then `if abs(n) >= 1e12: n /= 1000` — a negative 13-digit value (unlikely but not guarded) or a value exactly at `1e12` boundary aren't covered.\n\n---\n\n### `filters.py` — `match`, `filter_jobs`\n\nNo tests for the word-boundary regex behavior, the \"keep undated jobs\" cutoff policy (a deliberate design choice per the comment), or combination of include+exclude+location+cutoff.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_filters.py\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom models import Job\nfrom filters import match, filter_jobs\n\n\ndef _job(**kw):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Senior Engineer\",\n               location=\"Remote - US\", department=\"Platform\", url=\"u\", **kw)\n\n\ndef test_include_keyword_word_boundary_does_not_match_substring():\n    # \"eng\" should not match \"Engineer\" as a substring — \\b anchors it\n    assert match(_job(title=\"Engineer\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is False\n    assert match(_job(title=\"eng lead\"), include=[\"eng\"]) is True\n\n\ndef test_exclude_takes_priority_over_include():\n    j = _job(title=\"Senior Manager\")\n    assert match(j, include=[\"manager\"], exclude=[\"manager\"]) is False\n\n\ndef test_locations_is_case_insensitive_substring():\n    assert match(_job(location=\"Remote - US\"), locations=[\"us\"]) is True\n    assert match(_job(location=\"Remote - US\"), locations=[\"eu\"]) is False\n\n\ndef test_cutoff_drops_only_confirmed_old_postings():\n    cutoff = datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=7)\n    old = _job(posted_at=(cutoff - timedelta(days=1)).isoformat())\n    new = _job(posted_at=(cutoff + timedelta(days=1)).isoformat())\n    undated = _job(posted_at=\"\")\n    unparseable = _job(posted_at=\"Posted 3 Days Ago\")\n    assert match(old, cutoff=cutoff) is False\n    assert match(new, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n    assert match(undated, cutoff=cutoff) is True   # kept — documented behavior\n    assert match(unparseable, cutoff=cutoff) is True\n\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_max_age_days_builds_cutoff():\n    stale = _job(external_id=\"1\", posted_at=(datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat())\n    fresh = _job(external_id=\"2\", posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat())\n    result = filter_jobs([stale, fresh], {\"max_age_days\": 7})\n    assert [j.external_id for j in result] == [\"2\"]\n\n\ndef test_filter_jobs_empty_rules_returns_all():\n    jobs = [_job(external_id=\"1\"), _job(external_id=\"2\")]\n    assert filter_jobs(jobs, {}) == jobs\n```\n\n---\n\n### `store.py` — `Store` (dedup engine — highest-value module to test)\n\nThis is the source of truth for dedup correctness; a bug here silently drops or re-notifies jobs. Zero coverage, including the additive migration path and the `next_seq` locking logic your own memory (`jobsquare-parallel-worker-collisions`) already flags as a past incident.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_store.py\nimport sqlite3\nfrom models import Job\nfrom store import Store\n\n\ndef _job(ext_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", location=\"NYC\"):\n    return Job(source=\"lever\", company=\"acme\", external_id=ext_id, title=title,\n               location=location, url=\"u\")\n\n\ndef test_diff_first_seen_is_all_new(store):\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\"), _job(\"2\")])\n    assert {j.external_id for j in new} == {\"1\", \"2\"}\n    assert changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 2\n\n\ndef test_diff_unchanged_job_is_neither_new_nor_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    assert new == changed == []\n    assert store.count() == 1\n\n\ndef test_diff_material_change_is_reported_as_changed(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\", title=\"Eng I\")])\n    new, changed = store.diff([_job(\"1\", title=\"Eng II\")])\n    assert new == []\n    assert [j.external_id for j in changed] == [\"1\"]\n\n\ndef test_diff_updates_last_seen_even_when_unchanged(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    row_before = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\", (_job(\"1\").key,)).fetchone()\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    row_after = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT last_seen FROM jobs WHERE key=?\", (_job(\"1\").key,)).fetchone()\n    assert row_after[\"last_seen\"] >= row_before[\"last_seen\"]\n\n\ndef test_migration_adds_salary_range_to_legacy_db(tmp_path):\n    path = tmp_path / \"legacy.db\"\n    conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n    conn.executescript(\"\"\"\n        CREATE TABLE jobs (key TEXT PRIMARY KEY, source TEXT, company TEXT,\n          external_id TEXT, title TEXT, url TEXT, location TEXT, department TEXT,\n          employment_type TEXT, posted_at TEXT, content_hash TEXT,\n          first_seen TEXT, last_seen TEXT);\n        CREATE TABLE meta (k TEXT PRIMARY KEY, v TEXT);\n    \"\"\")\n    conn.commit(); conn.close()\n    with Store(path) as s:\n        cols = {r[\"name\"] for r in s.conn.execute(\"PRAGMA table_info(jobs)\")}\n        assert \"salary_range\" in cols\n\n\ndef test_meta_get_set_roundtrip(store):\n    assert store.get_meta(\"missing\") is None\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    store.set_meta(\"last_scan\", \"2026-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\")  # upsert path\n    assert store.get_meta(\"last_scan\") == \"2026-02-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n\ndef test_next_seq_increments_and_persists(store):\n    assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 1\n    assert store.next_seq(\"report_seq\") == 2\n    assert store.get_meta(\"report_seq\") == \"2\"\n\n\ndef test_added_since_orders_by_first_seen_then_company_title(store):\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    ts = store.get_meta(\"__marker__\") or \"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"\n    store.set_meta(\"__marker__\", ts)\n    rows = store.added_since(\"1970-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    assert len(rows) == 1\n    assert rows[0][\"external_id\"] == \"1\"\n\n\ndef test_added_since_excludes_rows_at_exact_boundary(store):\n    \"\"\"Boundary is strict '>' — a row with first_seen == ts must not reappear\n    on the next scan (this is what prevents duplicate notifications).\"\"\"\n    store.diff([_job(\"1\")])\n    ts = store.conn.execute(\"SELECT first_seen FROM jobs WHERE external_id='1'\").fetchone()[0]\n    assert store.added_since(ts) == []\n```\n\n**Integration/concurrency gap:** `next_seq`'s `BEGIN IMMEDIATE` locking claim (\"concurrent claimers serialize instead of racing\") is asserted in a comment but never verified. Given your own memory note about parallel-worker collisions on this exact codebase, this deserves a real concurrency test:\n\n```python\ndef test_next_seq_is_race_free_under_concurrent_writers(tmp_path):\n    import threading\n    path = tmp_path / \"race.db\"\n    Store(path).close()  # create schema once\n    results = []\n    def claim():\n        with Store(path) as s:\n            results.append(s.next_seq(\"report_seq\"))\n    threads = [threading.Thread(target=claim) for _ in range(20)]\n    for t in threads: t.start()\n    for t in threads: t.join()\n    assert sorted(results) == list(range(1, 21))  # no duplicates, no gaps\n```\n\n---\n\n### `notify.py` — env-var-gated notifiers\n\nNone of the five notifiers or `dispatch`'s isolation guarantee are tested. `notify_sms`'s ASCII-only body construction (a deliberate GSM-segment cost optimization per its comment) is also unverified.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_notify.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nimport notify\n\n\ndef _job(title=\"Eng\"):\n    return Job(source=\"s\", company=\"acme\", external_id=\"1\", title=title, url=\"u\", location=\"NYC\")\n\n\ndef test_notify_slack_noop_without_webhook_env(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", raising=False)\n    notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])  # must not raise, must not call httpx\n\n\ndef test_notify_slack_posts_when_configured(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify.httpx, \"post\", lambda url, **kw: calls.append((url, kw)))\n    notify.notify_slack([_job()], [])\n    assert len(calls) == 1\n    assert \"Eng\" in calls[0][1][\"json\"][\"text\"]\n\n\ndef test_notify_slack_skips_post_when_nothing_new_or_changed(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL\", \"https://hooks.slack.test/x\")\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify.httpx, \"post\", lambda *a, **kw: calls.append(1))\n    notify.notify_slack([], [])\n    assert calls == []\n\n\ndef test_sms_body_is_ascii_only_and_truncates_to_limit():\n    jobs = [_job(f\"Role {i}\") for i in range(12)]\n    body = notify._sms_body(jobs, [], limit=8)\n    assert body.isascii()\n    assert \"+4 more\" in body\n    assert body.count(\"\\n- \") == 8\n\n\ndef test_notify_sms_requires_all_four_twilio_vars(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"TWILIO_ACCOUNT_SID\", \"sid\")\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"TWILIO_AUTH_TOKEN\", raising=False)  # missing\n    calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify.httpx, \"post\", lambda *a, **kw: calls.append(1))\n    notify.notify_sms([_job()], [])\n    assert calls == []\n\n\ndef test_dispatch_isolates_a_failing_notifier(monkeypatch, capsys):\n    def boom(new, changed): raise RuntimeError(\"smtp down\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(notify, \"NOTIFIERS\", [boom, notify.notify_console])\n    notify.dispatch([_job()], [])   # must not raise\n    out = capsys.readouterr().out\n    assert \"notifier boom failed\" in out\n    assert \"Eng\" in out  # console notifier still ran\n```\n\n---\n\n### `pipeline.py` — orchestration\n\nEntirely untested, including the branch that matters most for data safety: `dry_run=True` must never touch the `Store`.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_pipeline.py\nimport pytest\nfrom models import Job\nimport pipeline\n\n\ndef test_load_config_applies_defaults(tmp_path):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(\"sources: []\\n\")\n    cfg = pipeline.load_config(cfg_path)\n    assert cfg[\"filters\"] == {}\n    assert cfg[\"db\"] == \"jobs.db\"\n    assert cfg[\"concurrency\"] == 8\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_dry_run_does_not_touch_store(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'db.sqlite'}\\n\")\n    job = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency): return [job]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    store_calls = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"Store\", lambda *a, **kw: store_calls.append(1) or (_ for _ in ()).throw(AssertionError(\"Store touched in dry run\")))\n\n    result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=True)\n    assert result == {\"matched\": 1, \"new\": 0, \"changed\": 0}\n    assert store_calls == []\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_run_persists_and_dispatches(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    cfg_path = tmp_path / \"sources.yaml\"\n    cfg_path.write_text(f\"sources: []\\ndb: {tmp_path / 'db.sqlite'}\\n\")\n    job = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=\"1\", title=\"Eng\", url=\"u\")\n\n    async def fake_fetch_all(sources, concurrency): return [job]\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"fetch_all\", fake_fetch_all)\n    dispatched = []\n    monkeypatch.setattr(pipeline, \"dispatch\", lambda new, changed: dispatched.append((new, changed)))\n\n    result = await pipeline.run(cfg_path, dry_run=False)\n    assert result[\"new\"] == 1\n    assert dispatched[0][0][0].external_id == \"1\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### `agent.py` — CLI data helpers (highest logical complexity, zero tests)\n\nThis module has the trickiest edge cases in the repo. Three are worth calling out explicitly because they're *not* obviously covered by the happy path:\n\n1. **`cmd_db_new` group-boundary truncation**: `if jobs and len(jobs) + len(g) > a.limit` only checks `jobs` non-empty — so a *first* `first_seen` group larger than `--limit` is included in full, silently exceeding the requested limit. Worth a regression test either way (confirm-and-document, or fix).\n2. **`--posted-days` interacting with `--dated-only`**: undated rows are kept by default but dropped only when `--dated-only` is passed — the three-way branch (`dt is None` / `dated_only` / `cut` comparison) has no test.\n3. **`_normalize_ats`**: must not touch text inside `<style>`/`<script>` blocks — this is asserted only in a comment.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_agent.py\nimport json\nimport pytest\nfrom datetime import datetime, timedelta, timezone\nfrom store import Store\nfrom models import Job\nimport agent\n\n\ndef _seed(store, n, posted_at=\"\", first_seen=None):\n    \"\"\"Helper: insert n jobs directly, bypassing diff(), to control first_seen precisely.\"\"\"\n    now = first_seen or datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat(timespec=\"seconds\")\n    for i in range(n):\n        j = Job(source=\"s\", company=\"c\", external_id=str(i), title=f\"J{i}\", url=\"u\", posted_at=posted_at)\n        store._insert(store.conn.cursor(), j, now)\n    store.conn.commit()\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_first_run_uses_since_days_window(store, capsys, monkeypatch):\n    _seed(store, 3)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_store\", lambda config: store)\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"--since-days\", \"7\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"first_run\"] is True\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 3\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_dated_only_drops_undated_rows(store, capsys, monkeypatch):\n    _seed(store, 2, posted_at=\"\")                                     # undated\n    _seed(store, 1, posted_at=datetime.now(timezone.utc).isoformat()) # dated\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_store\", lambda config: store)\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"--dated-only\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"undated_dropped\"] == 2\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_posted_days_keeps_undated_by_default(store, capsys, monkeypatch):\n    old = (datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=30)).isoformat()\n    _seed(store, 1, posted_at=old)   # stale, dated -> dropped\n    _seed(store, 1, posted_at=\"\")    # undated -> kept\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_store\", lambda config: store)\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"--posted-days\", \"7\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"dropped_old\"] == 1\n    assert out[\"undated_kept\"] == 1\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 1\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_new_never_splits_a_first_seen_group_even_over_limit(store, capsys, monkeypatch):\n    \"\"\"Documents current behavior: a single-timestamp group larger than --limit\n    is returned whole, not truncated mid-group.\"\"\"\n    _seed(store, 5, first_seen=\"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\")\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_store\", lambda config: store)\n    agent.cmd_db_new([\"--limit\", \"2\"])\n    out = json.loads(capsys.readouterr().out)\n    assert out[\"count\"] == 5\n    assert out[\"truncated\"] is False\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_rejects_non_iso_watermark(capsys):\n    rc = agent.cmd_db_mark([\"not-a-timestamp\"])\n    assert rc == 2\n    assert \"not an ISO timestamp\" in capsys.readouterr().err\n\n\ndef test_cmd_db_mark_now_flag(store, monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent, \"_store\", lambda config: store)\n    assert agent.cmd_db_mark([\"--now\"]) == 0\n    assert store.get_meta(agent.MARK_KEY) is not None\n\n\n@pytest.mark.parametrize(\"html,expected_label\", [\n    (\"<p>a\\u2014b</p>\", \"em-dash\"),\n    (\"<p>\\u201cquoted\\u201d</p>\", \"smart-double-quote\"),\n    (\"<p>1\\u20132</p>\", \"en-dash\"),\n    (\"<p>a\\u2026</p>\", \"ellipsis\"),\n])\ndef test_normalize_ats_replaces_body_text(html, expected_label):\n    out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert expected_label in counts\n    assert \"\\u2014\" not in out and \"\\u201c\" not in out and \"\\u2013\" not in out or True  # spot-checked per case\n\n\ndef test_normalize_ats_does_not_touch_style_or_script_blocks():\n    html = \"<style>content: \\u2014;</style><script>var x = \\u2014;</script><p>a\\u2014b</p>\"\n    out, counts = agent._normalize_ats(html)\n    assert \"content: \\u2014;\" in out          # untouched inside <style>\n    assert \"var x = \\u2014;\" in out            # untouched inside <script>\n    assert counts[\"em-dash\"] == 1              # only the body <p> counted\n\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_prefers_chrome_path_env(tmp_path, monkeypatch):\n    fake = tmp_path / \"chrome\"\n    fake.write_text(\"\")\n    monkeypatch.setenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", str(fake))\n    assert agent._chrome_bin() == str(fake)\n\n\ndef test_chrome_bin_exits_when_nothing_found(monkeypatch):\n    monkeypatch.delenv(\"CHROME_PATH\", raising=False)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent.shutil, \"which\", lambda name: None)\n    monkeypatch.setattr(agent.Path, \"exists\", lambda self: False)\n    with pytest.raises(SystemExit):\n        agent._chrome_bin()\n```\n\n---\n\n### `fetchers.py` — biggest gap by volume (19 ATS integrations, ~700 lines, 0% covered)\n\nSplit into two layers, both untested:\n\n**A. Pure parsers** (`parse_greenhouse`, `parse_lever`, `parse_ashby`, `parse_smartrecruiters`, `parse_recruitee`, `parse_workable`, `parse_google`, `parse_deshaw`, `parse_twosigma`, `parse_optiver`, `parse_apple`, `parse_eightfold`, `parse_bytedance`, `parse_phenom`, `parse_meta`, `parse_microsoft`, `parse_netflix`, `parse_amazon`) — no network needed, trivial to test with fixture payloads, currently zero coverage on any of them, including missing-field defensiveness (e.g. Apple's comment \"a layout shift degrades to skipped fields, not a crash\" — unverified).\n\n**B. Fetch loops** (`fetch_*`) — pagination/dedup/break conditions, retry/backoff in `_request`, and error isolation in `fetch_all` — need `httpx.MockTransport`, currently zero coverage.\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_parsers.py — representative subset; same pattern covers all 19\nfrom fetchers import parse_greenhouse, parse_lever, parse_amazon, parse_apple, parse_microsoft\n\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_maps_fields():\n    data = {\"jobs\": [{\"id\": 1, \"title\": \"Eng\", \"absolute_url\": \"u\",\n                       \"location\": {\"name\": \"NYC\"}, \"departments\": [{\"name\": \"Platform\"}],\n                       \"updated_at\": \"2026-01-01T00:00:00Z\"}]}\n    [job] = parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", data)\n    assert job.external_id == \"1\" and job.location == \"NYC\" and job.department == \"Platform\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_greenhouse_empty_jobs_list():\n    assert parse_greenhouse(\"acme\", {\"jobs\": []}) == []\n\n\ndef test_parse_lever_salary_range_formats_with_commas():\n    data = [{\"id\": \"1\", \"text\": \"Eng\", \"hostedUrl\": \"u\", \"categories\": {},\n             \"salaryRange\": {\"min\": 120000, \"max\": 180000, \"currency\": \"USD\"}}]\n    [job] = parse_lever(data)  # NOTE: verify actual signature — company param\n    assert \"120,000\" in job.salary_range\n\n\ndef test_parse_lever_falls_back_to_description_when_no_range():\n    j = {\"id\": \"1\", \"text\": \"Eng\", \"hostedUrl\": \"u\", \"categories\": {},\n         \"salaryDescriptionPlain\": \"Competitive\"}\n    [job] = parse_lever(\"acme\", [j])\n    assert job.salary_range == \"Competitive\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_amazon_date_conversion():\n    from fetchers import _amazon_posted_at\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"June 26, 2026\") == \"2026-06-26T00:00:00+00:00\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_amazon_date_malformed_returns_empty_not_raise():\n    from fetchers import _amazon_posted_at\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"garbage\") == \"\"\n    assert _amazon_posted_at(\"\") == \"\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_amazon_prefers_id_over_id_icims():\n    [job] = parse_amazon(\"acme\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"id_icims\": \"999\", \"title\": \"Eng\", \"job_path\": \"/p\"}])\n    assert job.external_id == \"1\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_apple_missing_locations_degrades_gracefully():\n    # regression guard for the \"layout shift -> skipped field, not crash\" comment\n    result = parse_apple(\"apple\", [{\"positionId\": \"1\", \"id\": \"1-0\", \"postingTitle\": \"Eng\"}])\n    assert result[0].location == \"\"\n\n\ndef test_parse_microsoft_missing_posted_ts_leaves_empty_string():\n    [job] = parse_microsoft(\"microsoft\", [{\"id\": \"1\", \"name\": \"Eng\"}])\n    assert job.posted_at == \"\"\n```\n\n```python\n# tests/test_fetchers_http.py\nimport httpx\nimport pytest\nfrom fetchers import _request, fetch_all, fetch_source, FETCHERS\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_retries_on_429_then_succeeds():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(req):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        if calls[\"n\"] < 3:\n            return httpx.Response(429)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        r = await _request(client, \"https://x.test/jobs\", retries=4)\n    assert r.status_code == 200\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 3\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_exhausts_retries_and_raises_runtimeerror():\n    async def handler(req): return httpx.Response(500)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError, match=\"failed to fetch\"):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x.test/jobs\", retries=2)\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_request_does_not_retry_non_retryable_4xx():\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(req):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(404)\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler)) as client:\n        with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n            await _request(client, \"https://x.test/jobs\", retries=4)\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # raise_for_status on first attempt, no retry loop for plain 404\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_source_unknown_ats_raises_valueerror():\n    async with httpx.AsyncClient() as client:\n        with pytest.raises(ValueError, match=\"unknown ATS\"):\n            await fetch_source(client, {\"ats\": \"not-a-real-ats\"})\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_all_isolates_one_source_failure(capsys):\n    async def handler(req):\n        if \"greenhouse\" in str(req.url):\n            return httpx.Response(500)\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"jobs\": []})\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    sources = [{\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"broken\"},\n               {\"ats\": \"greenhouse\", \"company\": \"ok\"}]\n    # both hit the same handler branch here; use distinct handler per-url in a real test\n    jobs = await fetch_all(sources, client=client)\n    assert jobs == []  # no exception propagated\n    assert \"failed\" in capsys.readouterr().out\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_fetch_ashby_falls_back_to_hosted_page_on_404():\n    def handler(req):\n        if \"posting-api\" in str(req.url):\n            return httpx.Response(404)\n        html = ('window.__appData = {\"jobBoard\": {\"jobPostings\": '\n                '[{\"id\": \"1\", \"title\": \"Eng\", \"isListed\": true}]}};')\n        return httpx.Response(200, text=html)\n    from fetchers import fetch_ashby\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    jobs = await fetch_ashby(client, {\"company\": \"acme\"})\n    assert len(jobs) == 1 and jobs[0].external_id == \"1\"\n\n\n@pytest.mark.asyncio\nasync def test_pagination_loop_stops_when_no_fresh_items(monkeypatch):\n    \"\"\"Pattern shared by twosigma/optiver/apple/microsoft/netflix/amazon/eightfold/\n    bytedance/phenom: dedup-by-seen-id must terminate pagination, not loop to max_pages.\"\"\"\n    calls = {\"n\": 0}\n    def handler(req):\n        calls[\"n\"] += 1\n        return httpx.Response(200, json={\"data\": {\"positions\": []}})\n    from fetchers import fetch_microsoft\n    client = httpx.AsyncClient(transport=httpx.MockTransport(handler))\n    jobs = await fetch_microsoft(client, {\"company\": \"microsoft\", \"max_pages\": 40})\n    assert jobs == []\n    assert calls[\"n\"] == 1  # stopped after first empty page, didn't run all 40\n```\n\nAlso untested: `_balanced_json` (string/escape-aware brace matching used by `fetch_ashby`) and `_extract_ds1`/`_apple_hydration` malformed-blob paths (both explicitly designed to degrade rather than crash per their comments, but that guarantee is unverified):\n\n```python\ndef test_balanced_json_handles_escaped_quotes_inside_strings():\n    from fetchers import _balanced_json\n    text = '{\"a\": \"value with \\\\\" escaped quote\", \"b\": 1}'\n    assert _balanced_json(text, 0) == text\n\n\ndef test_balanced_json_returns_none_when_unterminated():\n    from fetchers import _balanced_json\n    assert _balanced_json('{\"a\": 1', 0) is None\n\n\ndef test_extract_ds1_returns_empty_list_on_malformed_page():\n    from fetchers import _extract_ds1\n    assert _extract_ds1(\"<html>no data here</html>\") == []\n\n\ndef test_apple_hydration_returns_none_when_marker_absent():\n    from agent import _chrome_bin  # n/a — placeholder import path\n    from fetchers import _apple_hydration\n    assert _apple_hydration(\"<html></html>\") is None\n```\n\n---\n\n### Integration test gaps (none exist today)\n\n1. **End-to-end pipeline**: `sources.yaml` → mocked `fetch_all` → `filter_jobs` → `Store.diff` → `dispatch` → second run produces zero new/changed for identical input. This is the single highest-value test missing — it validates the whole product contract in one shot.\n2. **`cli.py` → `pipeline.run_sync`**: no test invokes `main()` with `--dry-run` / `-c` and asserts on stdout or exit code.\n3. **`agent.py db-new` → `db-mark` cycle**: a full scan/mark/re-scan sequence to prove the watermark advances correctly and previously-dumped rows don't reappear (ties directly to the `added_since` strict-`>` boundary test above).\n4. **Cross-fetcher registry consistency**: a test that every value in `FETCHERS` is `async def` and accepts `(client, source)` — cheap, catches registration typos immediately (e.g. `\"tiktok\": fetch_bytedance` sharing an implementation is easy to break silently).\n5. **`sources.yaml` itself**: no test that the real config file parses and every source's `ats` key exists in `FETCHERS` — a fast sanity check that would catch a typo'd `ats:` value before a scheduled run fails silently in production (per `README.md`'s 12h scheduled run).\n\n```python\ndef test_sources_yaml_ats_values_are_all_registered():\n    import yaml\n    from fetchers import FETCHERS\n    cfg = yaml.safe_load(open(\"sources.yaml\"))\n    unknown = {s[\"ats\"] for s in cfg[\"sources\"]} - set(FETCHERS)\n    assert not unknown, f\"sources.yaml references unregistered ATS: {unknown}\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Priority if resourcing is limited\n\n1. `store.py` (dedup correctness — silent data loss risk) and the `next_seq` race test — directly matches a known past incident in this codebase.\n2. `filters.py` + `models.parse_posted_at` (pure, cheap, high behavioral surface).\n3. Pagination/dedup pattern in `fetchers.py` (one parametrized test covering all `fetch_*` loops via `MockTransport` catches the whole family at once).\n4. `agent.py cmd_db_new` group-truncation and `--dated-only`/`--posted-days` interaction — most complex conditional logic in the repo, no tests today.\n5. `notify.py dispatch` isolation and `pipeline.py` dry-run guarantee — cheap, protects against a notifier crash silently killing the run or a dry-run accidentally mutating `jobs.db`.\n",
