        "title": "Test coverage analysis — jobsquare",
        "content": "\n**Baseline: 0%.** There is no `tests/` directory, no test files anywhere in the repo, and `pytest` isn't even in `requirements.txt`. Every one of the ~2,500 lines across `models.py`, `filters.py`, `store.py`, `pipeline.py`, `notify.py`, `cli.py`, `agent.py`, and `fetchers.py` (19 ATS integrations) is unexercised by automated tests.\n\nBelow: gaps by module, the specific edge cases the code already anticipates (via comments) but doesn't verify, and skeletons to close them. I'd suggest `pytest` + `pytest-asyncio` + `httpx.MockTransport` (no network needed) as the harness — add to `requirements.txt` / a new `requirements-dev.txt`.\n\n---\n\n",
